servings: 2
course: main course
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop the @shallot{1}. Strip the @thyme{1%sprig} leaves off the sprig, then roughly chop. Halve the @baby carrots{1%bunch} lengthwise. Peel the @potato{1}, then cut into 1/2-inch matchsticks (like French Fries!). In a #small bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} with @water{2%tablespoons}, then set aside.

Toss the carrots and potato on separate sides of a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Place the baking sheet in the oven and roast for ~{15-20%minutes}, tossing halfway through, until golden brown.

In a #medium bowl{}, thoroughly mix the @ground beef{12%ounce}, panko mixture, garlic, half the shallot, half the thyme, and a very large pinch salt (we used @kosher salt{1/2%teaspoon}) and pepper. Pack the mixture into the #loaf pan{} and top with @ketchup{1%tablespoon}. Bake for ~{15-20%minutes}, until cooked through.

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add the remaining shallot and cook, tossing, ~{3-4%minutes}, until softened. Sprinkle the @flour{2%tablespoon} into the pan and whisk constantly to combine. Whisk in the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup}, and the remaining thyme. Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}, until thickened. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if necessary.

Slice the meatloaf and serve with the roasted carrots and potato. Spoon a generous amount of shallot gravy over the meatloaf. Enjoy!